 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 221<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/24/03 10:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> More magery</span><hr size=1> All I want is a casting pet that is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;wizard-like&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in that it nukes, stuns, casts at a distance and does not melee.  Because I would like those nukes to land, I think it might be appropriate to have it cast <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;lure-like&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> spells,with a resist modifier.<br>
<br>
I do not want <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Ice Comet</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and I do not know the wizard spell line well enough to make informed suggestions.<br>
<br>
I prefer a sustained DPS pet that deals damage by casting at a distance, and that would be its specialty role.<br>
<br>
I suspect that a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;burst DPS&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->-type pet would be either ineffectual, or tread too closely on wizard territory.  Mages already can do some burst DPS, that is not exclusively the domain of wizards.  I think a discussion of a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;burst DPS&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> pet is appropriate, for what it reveals if nothing else.  But the domain of mages <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">is</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> sustained damage.<br>
<br>
It seems plausible to have the pet cast fire spells only, but I think that adding magic to the mix makes the pet more broadly useful.  Adding cold nukes, while counter-intuitive, may be okay since it is supposed to be wizard-like.<br>
<br>
I am tenatively opposed to snare, but the addition of snare may solve mage soloability problems.  However, I do not want to be a kiter.<br>
<br>
I think <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;wizard-lite&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is perhaps the best approach.  Clearly using wizard spells, with at least one that distinguishes from mages, but not intruding on wizard domains.<br>
<br>
