once pet dies its often time to run if hes solo<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->That is the one central fact around which mages are balanced.<br>
<br>
All the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;funny&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> effects for mages: stun, ice nukes, root, etc., are all accomplished only through pets.  By themselves, mages can only effect enemies by two means: hurting them by nukes, or debuffing via the malo-line of spells.<br>
<br>
Well there <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>is</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the new elemental charm and mezz, but these do not apply to the vast majority of the mage class, and are not considered central to mage identity.<br>
<br>
Some wizards here, I won't be specific, really need to learn how to read.  Far too many posters here take bits from here and there from various posts, stitch them together and conclude that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;mages....&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> whatever.<br>
